<DOC><DOCNO> AP880224-0250 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-24-88 0234EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Dominican-Protest     02-24 0237</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Dominican-Protest,0242</SECOND><HEAD>Reports Girl Killed in Anti-Government Protest</HEAD><DATELINE>SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A girl was shot andkilled Tuesday and three other people were wounded during ananti-government demonstration in the town of Azua, Radio Commercialreported.   It identified the slain girl as Mary Ramirez, 17, and said shewas shot in the head when protesters clashed with police andsoldiers in Azua, 75 miles west of Santo Domingo, the capital. Thebrodadcast said another youth, who was not identified, and twopolicemen hit by rocks were treated at hospitals.   Demonstrators had started their protest Monday, stoning cars andbusinesses to demand the government build more public worksprojects in the town.   Demonstrations also were reported Tuesday in two other towns,both involving claims of pollution by the government-owned Rosariogold mine north of Santo Domingo.   In Cotui, 60 miles north of the capital, 500 farmers joined theRev. Carlos Guerra in a protest at the town's Roman Catholicchurch, according to Radio Popular. It said the rally was held atthe end of a 72-hour general strike by Cotui residents.   A protest demonstration also was held in Bonao, 50 miles northof the capital, according to local news reports, but no detailswere given.   President Joaquin Balaguer declined comment on the latestdemonstrations. He said Sunday the disturbances were organized bypolitical opponents, but no oposition party has identified itselfwith the protests.</TEXT></DOC>